<unit id="1ca94560-70c8-4d69-b80d-f527ae85f6cf">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 8</note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>This addon was created following a request from a member on the nvda-addons mailing list.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="df3aced6-7e92-495f-ac12-9ff837c1dbf4">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 10</note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>It provides a script without gesture, which allows to retrieve and give the language of the current keyboard.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="ab0201a7-8814-4fe5-bc28-96c3652c8ec4">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 12</note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>If pressed twice, gives the default language of the system.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="b7807bed-9f0b-432b-9cd8-65097792c899">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 14</note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>At the first version of this module, it had been proposed as simple globalPlugin to paste in the configuration directory of NVDA, it was then transformed into addon.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="4181ca48-b609-441f-964a-c05c6c48c8e7">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 16</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: ## </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Notes ##</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="e89bc316-b972-4994-8fb6-7691960049ea">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 18</note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>To set a gesture to the script giving the keyboard language, follow these steps:</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="b583dbad-baef-44aa-aaa9-d8ca7e1bf0a0">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 20</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Open the NVDA's menu, with "NVDA + N";</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="01f514d4-b715-4eea-b57d-ca9a9d736ff6">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 21</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Go to NVDA's preferences menu;</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="1a38ad57-fd9d-4454-beff-f8d1d3489142">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 22</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Then go to the submenu "Input gestures".</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="5d4fb15f-b9ce-4bfa-8d8e-24134df76457">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 23</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Then select the category "Input", and open it with right arrow.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="377502b9-76be-4452-b965-7e4e18ca0f8d">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 24</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Go to the item labeled "Gives the language of the keyboard in use, if pressed twice, give the default language of the system";</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="c6b5770a-0b7f-432c-b7f4-4753f197cb11">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 25</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Once done, press Alt + A to add a gesture, and type "NVDA + F4" or another gesture of your choice;</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="f886f39a-6131-4517-bded-6cf740a1e26d">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 26</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>This done, press the up arrow once, you hear "your chosen gesture, all layout";</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="a322ac48-b60b-431f-8bb9-74eafd9e2ead">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 27</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Validate on enter, then tab to OK then enter;</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="a68005e0-7f1a-44e7-a6c3-1c633785932e">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 28</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Your chosen gesture should then call the script giving keyboard language.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
